value.title: AJAX Toolkit Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Execute any call in the API, and access any API object that you normally have access to by using the AJAX Toolkit — a JavaScript wrapper around the API.

value.title: Apex Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Learn about Salesforce Apex, the strongly typed, object-oriented, multitenant-aware programming language. Use Apex code to run flow and transaction control statements on the Salesforce platform. Apex syntax looks like Java and acts like database stored procedures. Developers can add business logic to most system events, including button clicks, related record updates, and Visualforce pages.

value.title: Apex Reference Guide
value.shortdesc: The Apex Reference of built-in Apex classes, interfaces, enums and exceptions, grouped by namespace. This guide also includes DML statements that you can use to insert, update, merge, delete, and restore data in Salesforce.

value.title: SOAP API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Build robust, server-side solutions that integrate your Salesforce data using SOAP API. Choose the Web Services Description Language (WSDL) that fits your need, whether it’s a strongly typed representation of your org’s data or a loosely typed representation that can be used to access data within any org.

value.title: Actions Developer Guide
value.subtitle: Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Action API provides APEX, SOAP, and REST interfaces that let you add quick actions to Salesforce applications. Actions let users quickly create or update records, log calls, send emails, and more, in the context of a particular object. For example, you add an object-specific action on the Account object that creates contacts. If someone creates a contact with that action on the detail page for the Acme account, that new contact is automatically associated with Acme.

value.title: Salesforce Reports and Dashboards REST API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: The Salesforce Reports and Dashboards REST API gives programmatic access to integrate reporting into a wide variety of applications. You can get report metadata, run reports synchronously or asynchronously to get summary data with or without details, filter report results on the fly, get a list of asynchronous runs for a report and results of each asynchronous run, and get a list of recently viewed reports.

value.title: Bulk API 2.0 and Bulk API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Quickly load your org’s data into Salesforce, or query large data sets with Bulk API.

value.title: Salesforce Console Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Learn how to extend, customize, and integrate the Salesforce console with a JavaScript API.

value.title: Open CTI Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Learn how to use a JavaScript API to build and integrate computer-telephony integration (CTI) systems with Salesforce.

value.title: Salesforce IoT REST API Getting Started Guide
Metadata API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Deploy customizations between Salesforce environments with Metadata API. Examples of customizations you can deploy include custom object definitions, page layouts, Apex code, and settings. Also, you can create, update, read, delete, and rename operations directly on metadata components.

value.title: Place Order REST API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Access your organization's order and contract data programmatically with the Salesforce Place Order REST API.

value.title: REST API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Build versatile and lightweight solutions that integrate your Salesforce data using REST API. This simple RESTful interface is powerful, convenient, and great for writing mobile and web apps.

value.title: Social Studio API Developer's Guide
value.shortdesc: Use the Social Studio API to author interesting new applications for extracting valuable marking information from the social media landscape

value.title: Streaming API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Receive notifications in a secure and scalable way with API Streaming. To receive notifications of changes to Salesforce data that match a SOQL query, use PushTopic Streaming. To deliver events with a payload of your choosing, use Generic Streaming.

value.title: Tooling API
value.subtitle: Reference and Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Integrate Salesforce with your other systems using Tooling API. Metadata types are exposed as sObjects, so you can access one component of a complex type. This field-level access speeds up operations on complex metadata types. You can also build custom development tools for Salesforce applications. REST and SOAP are both supported.

value.title: Application Installation Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to install a package from the AppExchange and roll out the package to your users.

value.title: AppExchange Publishing Guide (Deprecated)
value.shortdesc: Describes how to publish apps on the AppExchange, which is your complete marketplace for cloud computing applications and consulting partners.

value.title: Salesforce B2B2C Commerce Plug-In CLI Command Reference
value.shortdesc: Use CLI commands to create and manage applications on the Lightning Platform.

value.title: B2B Commerce on Lightning and B2B2C Commerce Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Design an integrated business-to-business and direct-to-consumer commerce solution that uses the power of Lightning Experience and Lightning Web Runtime.

value.title: Analytics Bindings Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to create bindings in CRM Analytics dashboards by modifying the JSON.

value.title: Salesforce Analytics Plugin CLI Command Reference
value.shortdesc: An alphabetized list of CLI commands that you use with Salesforce DX Analytics plugin to create and manage CRM Analytics assets on the Lightning Platform.

value.title: Analytics Dashboard Component Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to use the CRM Analytics Dashboard Component wave:waveDashboard beyond embedding it in a Salesforce page to increase interactive functionality

value.title: Analytics External Data API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to use the External Data API to upload CSV files to CRM Analytics and how to specify the structure of your data by defining metadata in JSON format.

value.title: Analytics External Data Format Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to prepare your external data files (CSV) and metadata files (JSON) before uploading them into a CRM Analytics dataset.

value.title: Analytics Dashboard JSON Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes the properties that can be included in the dashboard JSON. Modify the JSON properties to create advanced dashbards that aren’t possible using the CRM Analytics user interface.

value.title: Lightning Web Components in CRM Analytics Dashboards
value.shortdesc: Describes how to create and use custom Lightning Web Components in CRM Analytics Dashboards. Follow the step-by-step guide and use provided examples to get started on creating custom Lightning Web Component widgets that interact with the CRM Analytics widgets you know and love.

value.title: CRM Analytics REST API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to send queries directly to CRM Analytics, access datasets that have been imported into CRM Analytics, and create and retrieve lenses and dashboards.

value.title: Search Insights REST API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to find facts for datasets and interpert natural language queries.

value.title: Einstein Discovery REST API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to create and access Einstein Discovery predictions, discovery models, and stories.

value.title: Analytics SAQL Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to use the Salesforce Analytics Query Language (SAQL) to retrieve and analyze CRM Analytics data.

value.title: Analytics SDK Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to use CRM Analytics Lightning Web Components, CRM Analytics Assets and CRM Analytics Aura Component, CRM Analytics Aura Events, and CRM Analytics in Apex.

value.title: SQL for Analytics Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to use the CRM Analytics version of the SQL query language.

value.title: Analytics Templates Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Create CRM Analytics Templates from source apps, and downstream apps from templates.

value.title: Analytics Extended Metadata (XMD) Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to use extended metadata (XMD) to customize the formatting of dataset fields and their values in CRM Analytics dashboards and lenses.

value.title: Big Objects Implementation Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes the benefits of big objects, and details of creating, populating, and querying them.

value.title: Salesforce Billing Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Want to get started developing with Salesforce Billing? Check out developer guides, plugins, and Lightning components.

value.title: Einstein Bots Developer Cookbook
value.shortdesc: This cookbook covers some of the most popular use cases and frequently asked questions when building a bot that works for you.

value.title: Customer Data Platform Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Explore Salesforce CDP developer documentation, APIs, and resources to perform your customer data platform tasks programmatically.

value.title: Custom Address Fields (beta) Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Create and manage custom address fields. Access address data stored in these custom address fields with a structured compound data type and as individual address components.

value.title: Publisher and Quick Action Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Learn how you can use Lightning components, Visualforce, and Apex to customize your app’s experience, including the case feed.

value.title: Change Data Capture Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Receive near-real-time changes of Salesforce records, and synchronize corresponding records in an external data store. Change Data Capture publishes change events, which represent changes to Salesforce records.

value.title: Connect REST API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Integrate mobile apps, intranet sites, and third-party web applications with Salesforce using Connect REST API. Responses are localized, structured for presentation, and can be filtered to contain only what the app needs.

value.title: CMS Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Salesforce CMS is a hybrid content management system, where you can curate and share content, manage multiple language versions of your content, and control who creates what. See how to integrate CMS with other systems.

value.title: Experience Cloud Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Develop custom Aura components and theme layouts to meet your unique business needs and transform the look and feel of Experience Builder sites and Lightning Bolt Solutions.

value.title: Salesforce CPQ Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Start working with Salesforce CPQ API and plugins.

value.title: Salesforce CPQ Plugins
value.shortdesc: Want to start working with Salesforce CPQ plugins? Check out our definitions, use cases, and developer guides.

value.title: Ant Migration Tool Guide
value.shortdesc: Move metadata components between your Salesforce development and production orgs in an automated and repeatable way with the Ant Migration Tool. The Ant Migration Tool is a Java and Ant-based command-line utility.

value.title: A Guide to Sharing Architecture
value.shortdesc: Develop a sharing model for secure and efficient data access. Learn about data accessibility components, sharing model use cases, real customer sharing solutions, and troubleshooting guidelines.

value.title: Data Loader Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to use Data Loader, which is a client application for the bulk import or export of data. Use it to insert, update, delete, or export Salesforce or Database.com records.

value.title: Data.com API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: The Data.com APIs work with Salesforce Data.com Prospector and Data.com Clean to provide accurate account and contact data from Data.com.

value.title: Customer 360 Data Manager Data Jobs API Developer Guide
Designing Record Access for Enterprise Scale
value.shortdesc: Optimize your organization's record access control performance. Topics provide guidance on group maintenance, roles and object relationships for complex or large-scale organizations.

value.title: Force.com IDE Developer Guide (Retired)
value.shortdesc: The Force.com IDE Eclipse plugin is no longer available. Switch to using the Salesforce Extensions to Visual Studio Code.

value.title: Einstein Platform Services Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Use the Einstein Platform Services APIs to easily AI-enable your apps with image recognition and natural language processing. Using the Einstein Vision APIs, you can leverage pre-trained classifiers or train custom classifiers to solve a vast array of image recognition use cases. With the Einstein Language APIs, you can harness the power of natural language processing to analyze text and infer the sentiment or intent behind that text.

value.title: LWR Sites for Experience Cloud
value.shortdesc: Develop Experience Cloud sites that load quickly and scale well using the new Lightning Web Runtime (LWR) and the Lightning Web Components (LWC) programming model.

value.title: Salesforce External Identity Implementation Guide
value.shortdesc: Salesforce Identity can be used manage external identities, those of your customers and partners. The product is called Identity for Customers and Partners. Its license is called External Identity.

value.title: Field Audit Trail Implementation Guide
value.shortdesc: Field Audit Trail lets you define a policy to retain archived field history data up to ten years, independent of field history tracking. This feature helps you comply with industry regulations related to audit capability and data retention.

value.title: Field Service Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Build out your field service operation in Salesforce programmatically using Field Service objects in the SOAP, REST, Metadata, and Tooling APIs.

value.title: Using Date and Date/Time in Formulas
value.shortdesc: Learn how to use formulas to convert between date-related data types, how to work best with timezones, and how the TODAY(), NOW(), and DATE() functions work. We’ve included several useful examples to get you started.

value.title: Lightning Platform Fundamentals
value.subtitle: An Introduction to Custom Application Development in the Cloud
value.shortdesc: Get acquainted with the native functionality of the Lightning Platform by creating a recruiting application. Design and create objects, customize the app's user interface, control access to data, collaborate with Chatter, automate processes, and report on your data.

value.title: Customer 360 Data Manager Global Profile Lookup API Developer Guide
Industries Common Resources Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: This guide contains developer documentation for features that are available in two or more Industries clouds.

value.title: Integration Patterns and Practices
value.shortdesc: Discover strategies for integrating Lightning Platform with other applications through specific scenarios.

value.title: Chatter Answers JavaScript API Reference
value.shortdesc: The Chatter Answers JavaScript API helps you mediate communication to the Chatter Answers UI. Learn the standard events and methods that you can use to customize the behavior of Chatter Answers UI components.

value.title: Salesforce Knowledge Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Build a robust knowledge base with SOAP API, REST API, Metadata API, SOQL, SOSL, and Apex.

value.title: Lightning Aura Components Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Create Aura components for Salesforce for Android, iOS, and mobile web and Lightning Experience with JavaScript and Apex. Components can be used in standalone apps, Visualforce, Lightning App Builder, and Experience Builder.

value.title: Service Cloud Chat Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Create customized chat windows, buttons, forms, and pages for your company's Chat configuration.

value.title: Chat REST API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Take Chat beyond your website: Extend chats to native mobile apps with the Chat REST API.

value.title: Loyalty Management Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Loyalty Management gives you the tools and developer resources you need to create and run a loyalty program in Salesforce.

value.title: Lightning Web Components Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Use Lightning Web Components to develop apps using a standards-driven JavaScript model.

value.title: Salesforce Maps Apex Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Apex developer guide for technical admins and developers using Salesforce Maps.

value.title: Messaging Object Model
value.shortdesc: Guide for developers using the Service Cloud Messaging feature.

value.title: Net Zero Cloud Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Net Zero Cloud gives you critical insights about your carbon footprint.

value.title: Object Reference for the Salesforce Platform
value.shortdesc: Get details on standard objects so that you can interface with your Salesforce data.

value.title: Set Up Omni-Channel Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Customize your Omni-Channel records and console integration with Omni-Channel API objects and console methods.

value.title: Salesforce Order Management Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Customize Salesforce Order Management and integrate it with your storefront, inventory, and fulfillment systems.

value.title: ISVforce Guide
value.shortdesc: Plan, build, and sell AppExchange solutions and consulting services.

value.title: Visualforce Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Learn how to develop custom user interfaces and apps with Visualforce, a framework that allows developers to build and deploy custom functionality hosted natively on the Lightning Platform.

value.title: Canvas Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Learn how to integrate third-party applications into Salesforce using the Canvas framework.

value.title: Platform Encryption REST API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: The REST API for Salesforce Platform Encryption lets you generate and manage tenant secrets outside of Salesforce.

value.title: Platform Events Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Use platform events to connect business processes in Salesforce and external apps through the exchange of real-time event data. Platform events are secure and scalable messages that contain data. Publishers publish event messages that subscribers receive in real time. To customize the data published, define platform event fields.

value.title: Salesforce Mobile Notifications Implementation Guide
value.shortdesc: Keep your mobile users informed of important news in your organization by implementing notifications. Notifications let enabled mobile devices receive alerts, tips, and encrypted data from Salesforce.

value.title: Restriction Rules Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Restriction rules let you enhance security and protect your data by allowing specified users to have access only to designated records.

value.title: Salesforce Mobile App Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Discover both the declarative (point-and-click) and the programmatic (code-based) features of Salesforce. Learn how you can optimize existing features such as Visualforce pages and quick actions for the Salesforce mobile experience, as we walk you through the process of making an existing organization mobile-ready.

value.title: Salesforce Developer Limits and Allocations Quick Reference
value.shortdesc: Find the most critical limits for developing Lightning Platform applications.

value.title: Campaign Management Implementation Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes the steps needed to set up and use campaign management.

value.title: Sample CRM Dashboards
value.shortdesc: This guide highlights some of the great features available in Salesforce dashboards and reports, and includes tips on getting the most out of your dashboard components.

value.title: Setting Up Your .NET Developer Environment
value.shortdesc: Configure your local dev environment for integrating with Salesforce using .NET.

value.title: Setting Up Your Java Developer Environment
value.shortdesc: Configure your local dev environment for integrating with Salesforce using Java.

value.title: Lightning Flow for Service Developer Guide
value.tagline: Guide your users with a list of actions
value.shortdesc: Associate records to actions and guide your users through multi-step processes in your Lightning apps

value.title: Best Practices for Deployments with Large Data Volumes
value.shortdesc: Improve the performance of applications with large data volumes, and Salesforce mechanisms that affect or support the performance of systems with large data volumes.

value.title: Design Without Limits
value.shortdesc: Learn how to make your apps lean and limitless for a large customer base with these strategies for eight different app design scenarios.

value.title: Lightning Platform Glossary
value.shortdesc: Get acquainted with terms that are specific to Lightning Platform.

value.title: Salesforce Sites Implementation Guide
value.shortdesc: Describes how to use Salesforce Sites, which enables you to create public websites and applications that are directly integrated with your Salesforce organization.

value.title: Record-Level Access: Under the Hood
value.shortdesc: See different levels of data access, as well as table-level ("under the hood") views of record-level access. Prepare yourself to give the right users the right access to the right records at the right time — and do so in the fastest time possible.

value.title: Using the Reports Tab
value.shortdesc: The Reports tab makes it easier to find, organize, and manage both your reports and dashboards in one place.

value.title: Sample Approval Processes
value.shortdesc: Review samples of common approval processes to help you get started creating your own.

value.title: Visualforce Performance: Best Practices
value.shortdesc: Create Visualforce pages that perform well by following these best practices. Diagnose page performance issues by using these troubleshooting techniques.

value.title: Scoping Rules Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Scoping rules let you control the default records that your users see based on criteria that you select.

value.title: Secure Coding Guide
value.shortdesc: Learn how to avoid the most common security issues that Salesforce has identified while auditing applications built on or integrated with the Lightning Platform.

value.title: Salesforce Security Guide
value.shortdesc: Implement your own security policies to protect your Salesforce org. Increase trust by confirming user identity, controlling access to specific apps and data, sharing objects and field data securely, encrypting data, and auditing changes.

value.title: Salesforce Field Reference Guide
value.shortdesc: Use this concise reference to quickly look up details of the standard fields for most of the major objects in Salesforce.

value.title: Salesforce CLI Plug-In Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Discover how to develop your own plug-ins for Salesforce CLI. Explore the Salesforce CLI architecture. Learn how to generate a plug-in using Salesforce Plug-In Generator, use Salesforce’s libraries to add functionality to your plug-in, and debug issues. Learn about our suggested style guidelines for naming and messages and our recommended best practices for plug-ins.

value.shortdesc: An alphabetized list of CLI commands that you use with Salesforce DX to create and manage applications on the Lightning Platform.

value.title: Salesforce DX Developer Guide

Set up a project, create a scratch org and source files, synchronize code changes between your org and version control system, continuously test and integrate, and package your app for release.

value.title: Salesforce CLI Setup Guide
value.shortdesc: Learn how to install the Salesforce CLI.

value.title: Embedded Service for Web Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: Improve the functionality of your Embedded Service deployment by customizing parameters in the Embedded Service code snippet, adding JavaScript, or using an Lightning Web or Aura Components

value.title: SOQL and SOSL Reference
value.shortdesc: Query and search your org’s data for specific information with Salesforce Object Query Language and Salesforce Object Search Language.

value.title: User Interface API Developer Guide
value.shortdesc: User Interface API enables you to create native mobile apps and custom web apps with your own branding and look and feel. A single REST request returns enough metadata, layout information, and data to display, edit, or create a record.

value.title: Examples of Advanced Formula Fields
value.shortdesc: Review examples of formula fields for various types of apps that you can use and modify for your own purposes.

value.title: Examples of Validation Rules
value.shortdesc: Review examples of validation rules for various types of apps that you can use and modify for your own purposes. Validation rules verify that the data a user enters in a record meets the standards you specify before the user can save the record.

value.title: Examples of Workflow Rules

value.title: Federated Search Developer Guide

The Federated Search API connects a Salesforce federated search connector to the external search provider so that data from external repositories can be searched and returned within Salesforce. External search providers have partnered with Salesforce to provide a search service that conforms to our API.
